  "description": "This morning dish leans on traditional South Indian technique but shifts the grain balance toward whole grains and lentils. Saamai Vegetable Kichadi brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Heat oil in a cooker or heavy pot on medium heat. Add mustard, cumin, and curry leaves; once aromatic, add onion, ginger, chilli, and vegetables and cook 3 minutes.",
    "Add the grain, dal, salt, and water and bring to a boil over high heat.",
    "Pressure cook for 3 whistles or cover and cook on low heat for 18 to 20 minutes until the grain is soft and spoonable.",
    "Rest 5 minutes, then stir briskly once to unify the starch and vegetables before serving."
  ],
